"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-interactive-2024-07-25-magazine-olympics-surfing-teahupoo-french-polynesia.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"By Talya MinsbergPhotographs and videos by Ben ThouardAnimations by Kyutae Lee The surf at the Tokyo Olympics was unremarkable at best, with conditions that could be described as unpredictable slosh.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9940425824257257, \"rank\": 0.005993050603297188, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Talya MinsbergPhotographs\", \"from\": 3, \"to\": 28}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"Ben ThouardAnimations\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 64}, {\"ngram\": \"The surf\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 87}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 109}, {\"ngram\": \"conditions\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 151}, {\"ngram\": \"unpredictable slosh\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was nearly impossible for competitors to show the kind of awe-inspiring surfing techniques they were capable of.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 316, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"awe-inspiring surfing techniques\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers for the Paris Olympics sought to change that.\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 327}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So this year's surf competition will take place 10,000 miles away, off the coast of Tahiti in French Polynesia, at Teahupo'o - one of the most dangerous and deadly surf breaks in the world.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 458, \"end\": 464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999979418135, \"rank\": 2.0580807223768997e-09, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 475, \"end\": 484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9976431152250816, \"rank\": 0.0023624528040204567, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this year's surf competition\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"the coast\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"the most dangerous and deadly surf\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The waves at Teahupo'o - which roughly translates to \\\"wall of skulls\\\" - can range from five feet to a death-defying 50 feet.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 689, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The waves\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"to \\\"wall\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"skulls\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 633}, {\"ngram\": \"five feet\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"a death-defying 50 feet\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you use a ski or snowboard analogy, it's not even a double black diamond run,\\\" Kevin Wallis, the director of forecasting at Surfline, a surf forecasting site, says.\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfline\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Surfline\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfline\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfline\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ski or snowboard analogy\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"even a double black diamond run\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"Kevin Wallis\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"the director\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"forecasting\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 814}, {\"ngram\": \"a surf forecasting site\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's like going into the Alaskan backcountry and riding some huge mountain.\\\"\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Alaskan backcountry\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"some huge mountain\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the goal at the last Olympic surfing contest was to score big on highly technical maneuvers like aerials, the goal at this year's games will be to simply survive.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Olympic surfing contest\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"highly technical maneuvers\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"aerials\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's games\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before each round of competition, a motorized personal watercraft will take surfers about half a mile offshore, where they will wait for the perfect wave.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each round\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1136}, {\"ngram\": \"a motorized personal watercraft\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect wave\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They need to be correctly positioned so that they can begin paddling and then drop into the wave at precisely the right moment.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"precisely the right moment\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If they survive that drop, they will be trying to slide down a wall of water and maneuver themselves directly into the wave's belly.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that drop\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"a wall\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave's belly\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfers who make it into the barrel find themselves with a powerful wall of water overhead \\u2026 \\u2026 and less than knee-deep water between them and the sharp coral reef below.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Surfers\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"the barrel\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful wall\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"knee-deep water\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"the sharp coral reef\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If any one thing goes wrong - and something often does - the surfers are in for a beating.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any one thing\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"the surfers\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"a beating\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the competitors, there is very little room for error.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competitors\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"very little room\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1831}, {\"ngram\": \"error\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1841}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's like being in a massive tumble dryer or washing machine, but with reef,\\\" Jack Robinson, an Australian Olympic surfer, says.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.9999779164496527, \"rank\": 2.207734104616748e-05, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.9434730725947648, \"rank\": 0.05947161767050369, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1940, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9876555420954823, \"rank\": 0.01249874243231677, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a massive tumble dryer\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"washing machine\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"reef\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1919}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tremendous power and weight of the wave can send surfers whirling through air and water before they are held down under several successive waves or dragged over the sharp reef.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tremendous power\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"weight\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2034}, {\"ngram\": \"air\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2065}, {\"ngram\": \"several successive waves\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"the sharp reef\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The luckiest shake off the wipeout and return to the competition.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2220, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The luckiest shake\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2173}, {\"ngram\": \"the wipeout\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But others at Teahupo'o have suffered head injuries, punctured lungs, broken ribs or gashes that demand dozens of stitches.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2231}, {\"ngram\": \"head injuries\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\": \"punctured lungs\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"broken ribs\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"gashes\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"stitches\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many have nearly drowned; and a few have even been killed.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For those who have not surfed much in French Polynesian waters, the peaceful and picturesque setting - a quiet fishing village, surrounded by lush mountains, with a soft mist often settling in the valley between them - can disguise the dramatic conditions of Teahupo'o's ocean floor, which make the surf both exhilarating and tremendously dangerous.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2443, \"end\": 2449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9534043942024464, \"rank\": 0.04885840981371138, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the peaceful and picturesque setting\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"a quiet fishing village\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2531}, {\"ngram\": \"lush mountains\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"a soft mist\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"the valley\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"the dramatic conditions\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2660}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o's ocean floor\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2687}, {\"ngram\": \"the surf\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2708}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Less than a half mile off shore, the water is some 1,000 feet deep.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shore\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2787}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the deep, open ocean abruptly meets the shallow reef below, a wall of water juts up, creating the heavy, hollow barrel of the wave.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2961, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the deep, open ocean\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2850}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"a wall\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2896}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"the heavy, hollow barrel\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2948}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simultaneously, the water receding from the shore helps create the \\\"curl\\\" that most people think of when they picture a wave.\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 3088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2988}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3012}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"curl\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To exit the wave, a surfer needs to maneuver their board to avoid getting knocked down by the spit of the barrel as it closes.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3216, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfer\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3116}, {\"ngram\": \"their board\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"the spit\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3188}, {\"ngram\": \"the barrel\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing is the only Olympic sport that depends entirely on day-to-day forecasting.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3300, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only Olympic sport\", \"from\": 3229, \"to\": 3251}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 3284, \"to\": 3287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the course of a 10-day holding period, from July 27 to Aug. 5, a team of forecasters will assess the likely surf conditions throughout each day to determine the most suitable time for competition.\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3316}, {\"ngram\": \"a 10-day holding period\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3343}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3354}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug.\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3365}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3375}, {\"ngram\": \"forecasters\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3390}, {\"ngram\": \"the likely surf conditions\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3429}, {\"ngram\": \"each day\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3449}, {\"ngram\": \"the most suitable time\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3485}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On any given day, the Tahitian government could issue a Code Red, designating the surf as too dangerous for athletes and watercraft.\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3525, \"end\": 3533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999968895281, \"rank\": 3.110328967493645e-09, \"text\": \"Tahitian\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any given day\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3519}, {\"ngram\": \"a Code Red\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3567}, {\"ngram\": \"the surf\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3589}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3619}, {\"ngram\": \"watercraft\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or there could be a swell so small that forecasters worry about a lack of Olympic-worthy waves.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3731, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a swell\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"forecasters\", \"from\": 3676, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 3700, \"to\": 3706}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic-worthy waves\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Riding Teahupo'o, Brisa Hennessy, an Olympic surfer from Costa Rica, says, is \\\"riding this wave of heaven and death.\\\"\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3751, \"end\": 3765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisa_Hennessy\", \"score\": 0.9999999726242098, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brisa Hennessy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisa_Hennessy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisa_Hennessy\"}, {\"begin\": 3790, \"end\": 3800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costa_Rica\", \"score\": 0.9999999989145181, \"rank\": 1.085550512494963e-09, \"text\": \"Costa Rica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costa_Rica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costa_Rica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Riding Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3749}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic surfer\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3784}, {\"ngram\": \"this wave\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3828}, {\"ngram\": \"heaven\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3838}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 3843, \"to\": 3848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When they discuss what it will take to win these Olympics, they speak not just of training regimens but also of the essence of the place itself.\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3995, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3908}, {\"ngram\": \"training regimens\", \"from\": 3933, \"to\": 3950}, {\"ngram\": \"the essence\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 3974}, {\"ngram\": \"the place\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To surf Teahupo'o is to respect Teahupo'o - and to surf Teahupo'o well is to connect deeply with the land, the sea and the people around it.\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4037}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4061}, {\"ngram\": \"the land\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4101}, {\"ngram\": \"the sea\", \"from\": 4103, \"to\": 4110}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's very, very humbling,\\\" Carissa Moore, an American gold medalist, says.\", \"from\": 4137, \"to\": 4212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4165, \"end\": 4178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carissa Moore\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 4183, \"end\": 4191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999993579960815, \"rank\": 6.242124720294373e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"very, very humbling\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The minute you do not respect mother nature, it's going to swipe you off your feet.\\\"\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mother nature\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4257}, {\"ngram\": \"your feet\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Talya Minsbergis a reporter covering fitness and wellness for The Times.\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4362, \"end\": 4371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.772927529391734e-12, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Talya Minsbergis\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4316}, {\"ngram\": \"a reporter\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4327}, {\"ngram\": \"fitness\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"wellness\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has reported on the Olympics in Pyeongchang, Tokyo and Beijing.\", \"from\": 4373, \"to\": 4440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4409, \"end\": 4420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\", \"score\": 0.9999741784272901, \"rank\": 2.5822239593928144e-05, \"text\": \"Pyeongchang\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pyeongchang_County\"}, {\"begin\": 4422, \"end\": 4427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9970015565724953, \"rank\": 0.002107208754371119, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 4432, \"end\": 4439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7905116007168619, \"rank\": 0.2650034923299734, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4393, \"to\": 4405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ben Thouardis a photographer in Tahiti, originally from France.\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4474, \"end\": 4480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999979418135, \"rank\": 2.0580807223768997e-09, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 4498, \"end\": 4504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996450601001131, \"rank\": 0.00014445720226047816, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ben Thouardis\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4455}, {\"ngram\": \"a photographer\", \"from\": 4456, \"to\": 4470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been creating images of the ocean since he was a teenager.\", \"from\": 4506, \"to\": 4571, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4533}, {\"ngram\": \"the ocean\", \"from\": 4537, \"to\": 4546}, {\"ngram\": \"a teenager\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author of two books of photography, ''Surface'' and ''Turbulences.''\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4650, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the author\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4588}, {\"ngram\": \"two books\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4601}, {\"ngram\": \"photography\", \"from\": 4605, \"to\": 4616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}]}"